## Introduction

TypeScript adds static typing to JavaScript, which can help you write more reliable and maintainable React code.

## Tip 1: Type Your Props

```tsx
interface ButtonProps {
  label: string;
  onClick: () => void;
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
}

export function Button({ label, onClick, variant = 'primary' }: ButtonProps) {
  return <button onClick={onClick}>{label}</button>;
}
```

## Tip 2: Use Generic Hooks

```tsx
function useLocalStorage<T>(key: string, initialValue: T) {
  // ...
}
```

## Tip 3: Discriminated Unions for State

```tsx
type State =
  | { status: 'idle' }
  | { status: 'loading' }
  | { status: 'success'; data: Article[] }
  | { status: 'error'; message: string };
```

These patterns will make your codebase much more robust!
